'''Bizorędki''' {{IPAc-pl|b|i|z|o|'|r|e|n|d|k|i}} is a [[village]] in the administrative district of [[Gmina Sobków]], within [[Jędrzejów County]], [[Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship]], in south-central Poland. It lies approximately {{convert|10|km|mi|0}} north-west of [[Sobków]], {{convert|14|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} north of [[Jędrzejów]], and {{convert|25|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-west of the regional capital [[Kielce]].<ref name="TERYT">{{cite web |url=http://www.stat.gov.pl/broker/access/performSearch.jspa?searchString=Bizor%C4%99dki+&level=miejsc&wojewodztwo=2219&powiat=&gmina=&miejscowosc=&advanced=true |title=Central Statistical Office (GUS) - TERYT (National Register of Territorial Land Apportionment Journal) |date=2008-06-01 |language=Polish}}</ref>
Adjacents with [[Bizoręda]].

== History ==
In 1827 y. was 12 houses and 60 villagers.<ref name="SgKP">{{SgKP|XV_cz.1|160|Bizorędki}}</ref>
